title: Adani Group stocks under ASM stage-1 category: What it means for shareholders
summary: This article reports that two Adani Group stocks, Adani Green Energy and Adani Energy Solutions, have been placed under the first stage of the Bombay Stock Exchange's (BSE) long-term Additional Surveillance Measures (ASM) framework. This action, initiated by SEBI (Securities and Exchange Board of India), is due to high stock volatility following a US indictment of Gautam Adani and others on bribery and fraud charges related to securing solar contracts. The ASM framework, designed to protect investors, involves two stages with minimum trading session durations before review, and mandates 100% margin blocking in the trade-to-trade segment. title: Wall Street today: US stock indices mixed after PCE inflation data
summary: This Livemint article reports on mixed reactions in the US stock market following the release of October's Personal Consumption Expenditure (PCE) inflation data.
